PhonePe Payment Gateway v2 (UPI) — FastAPI + React Integration Playbook

Prerequisites and contacts

- Register as a PhonePe merchant on the PhonePe merchant/developer portal and complete KYC to receive your Merchant ID, Client/Secret credentials and Salt Key/Salt Index for v2 integrations [PhonePe Payment Gateway API Documentation](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-integration-website).

Environment & base URLs

- Sandbox (UAT) base URL: https://api-preprod.phonepe.com/apis/pgsandbox [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).
- Production base URLs: Authorization API at https://api.phonepe.com/apis/identity-manager/ and PG APIs at https://api.phonepe.com/apis/pg/ [PhonePe Payment Gateway API Documentation](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-integration-website).

Installations / Dependencies

FastAPI backend (Python)

- Python 3.9+ recommended. Install core packages:
  - fastapi
  - uvicorn
  - requests
  - python-dotenv (for local env management)
  - optional: the official PhonePe Python BE SDK if you prefer the SDK wrapper (see SDK docs)

Example pip install:

pip install fastapi uvicorn requests python-dotenv

(Official PhonePe Python SDK and integration steps referenced at PhonePe backend SDK docs) [PhonePe Python SDK Integration Steps](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/backend-sdk/python-be-sdk/integration-steps).

React frontend

- React 18+ and axios (or fetch) for HTTP calls.

Example npm install:

npm install axios react-router-dom

Note: PhonePe provides a React Native SDK package for mobile (react-native-phonepe-pg) but for web you will use the hosted PayPage iframe/redirect flow [React Native SDK Setup](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/mobile-app-integration/standard-checkout-mobile/react-native/sdk-setup) and Web integration docs for the PayPage snippet [Invoke iframe PayPage](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-reference/invoke-iframe-paypage).

API Keys and security best practices

- Obtain the following from PhonePe after merchant onboarding: Merchant ID, Client ID, Client Secret, Salt Key, Salt Index, and webhook username/password (for callback auth) [PhonePe Payment Gateway API Documentation](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-integration-website).

- Never expose secrets in client-side code. Store secrets server-side only and load via environment variables or a secrets manager (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault). Use HTTPS for all communications [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).

- Use separate credentials for Sandbox and Production. Do not mix sandbox credentials with production endpoints; this is a common cause of "resource not found" errors when migrating to live [Troubleshooting | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/troubleshooting) and community reports [Stack Overflow migration issue](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/77207378/issues-in-migrating-to-live-mode-phonepe-payment-gateway).

X-VERIFY checksum header (generation and verification)

PhonePe v2 requires an X-VERIFY header on certain calls as a checksum to validate payload integrity. The canonical algorithm and exact formatting are documented by PhonePe — follow these steps when generating X-VERIFY for request bodies:

1. Serialize the request body to compact JSON (no spaces). 2. Base64-encode the JSON string. 3. Concatenate: base64(payload) + API_PATH + SALT_KEY. 4. Compute SHA256 of that concatenated string and take the uppercase hex digest. 5. Append '###' + SALT_INDEX to form the final X-VERIFY value.

This procedure is described in PhonePe's X-VERIFY calculation guide [Calculating X-VERIFY](https://developer.phonepe.com/switch/documentation/calculating-x-verify).

Sample Python implementation (FastAPI-ready)

- This example demonstrates token acquisition (OAuth), X-VERIFY generation (per PhonePe docs), create-payment, status check, and webhook handling. Replace environment variables with your real credentials.

