Notes / explanation for backend code

- Token acquisition: the backend exchanges client_id/client_secret for an OAuth access token; store and reuse until expiry rather than fetching every call [PhonePe Auth API docs](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-integration-website).
- X-VERIFY: the algorithm used above follows PhonePe's documented method and must be applied exactly to the request body and API path for requests that require the header [Calculating X-VERIFY](https://developer.phonepe.com/switch/documentation/calculating-x-verify).
- Webhook validation: PhonePe uses Basic auth (Authorization header with base64 username:password); verify that header and process events [Webhook Handling | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/mobile-app-integration/standard-checkout-mobile/webhook-handling).

Frontend (React web) — minimal integration pattern

- Approach: frontend requests the backend to create a payment order, backend returns a tokenUrl (hosted PayPage URL) or the response required for invoking the hosted PayPage, then frontend invokes the PhonePe checkout JS to open the iframe or redirect user to PayPage.

