React component example (calls backend and redirects)

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import axios from 'axios';
import { useLocation } from 'react-router-dom';

function useQuery() {
  return new URLSearchParams(useLocation().search);
}

export default function PhonePePayment() {
  const [amount, setAmount] = useState(100); // rupees
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [status, setStatus] = useState(null);
  const query = useQuery();

  useEffect(() => {
    const txn = query.get('txnId');
    const st = query.get('status');
    if (txn && st) setStatus(st);
  }, [query]);

  const startPayment = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      const resp = await axios.post('/api/payment/initiate', {
        merchantOrderId: `order-${Date.now()}`,
        amount: amount * 100,
        redirectUrl: `${window.location.origin}/payment-callback`
      });

      const tokenUrl = resp.data.redirectUrl || resp.data.paymentUrl || resp.data.tokenUrl;
      if (!tokenUrl) throw new Error('No payment URL from backend');

      // Use PhonePe Checkout JS if present (iframe mode), otherwise redirect
      if (window.PhonePeCheckout) {
        window.PhonePeCheckout.transact({ tokenUrl, callback: (r) => console.log('PhonePe callback', r), type: 'IFRAME' });
      } else {
        window.location.href = tokenUrl; // fallback redirect
      }
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      alert('Payment initiation failed');
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <h3>PhonePe UPI Payment</h3>
      <label>
        Amount (₹):
        <input type="number" value={amount} onChange={(e) => setAmount(Number(e.target.value))} />
      </label>
      <button onClick={startPayment} disabled={loading}>{loading ? 'Processing...' : 'Pay with PhonePe'}</button>
      {status && <p>Payment status: {status}</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Testing procedures (Sandbox)

- Use the PhonePe UAT sandbox host for all test requests: https://api-preprod.phonepe.com/apis/pgsandbox [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).

- PhonePe provides a Test App (Android package com.phonepe.simulator) to simulate UPI flows and choose Success/Failure/Pending outcomes during QR or intent flows [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).

- Test card data (for card flows) and OTPs (e.g., OTP 123456) are provided by PhonePe’s sandbox docs for simulating card/netbanking transactions [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).

- Test cases to run:
  - Create payment (expected: redirectUrl/tokenUrl returned). Verify frontend opens PayPage. [PayPage invocation docs](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-reference/invoke-iframe-paypage).
  - Complete payment in PhonePe Test App and verify webhook (checkout.order.completed) and/or poll order status endpoint return success [Webhook Handling | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/mobile-app-integration/standard-checkout-mobile/webhook-handling).
  - Simulate user cancel and ensure your callback and order status reflect 'USER_CANCEL' or failure.
  - Attempt refund and refund status flows in sandbox to validate refund API integration.

Common pitfalls and mitigations

- Mixing sandbox and production credentials or endpoints causes 404/RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND errors; ensure environment-specific configuration [Troubleshooting | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/troubleshooting) and community reports [Stack Overflow migration issue](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/77207378/issues-in-migrating-to-live-mode-phonepe-payment-gateway).

- Incorrect X-VERIFY generation (wrong path, payload serialization, salt, or saltIndex) will lead to checksum validation failures; follow the exact sequence in the official X-VERIFY guide and test with the sandbox [Calculating X-VERIFY](https://developer.phonepe.com/switch/documentation/calculating-x-verify).

- CORS and browser-origin issues: do not call PhonePe server APIs directly from browser — always route through your backend which holds secrets and tokens [Troubleshooting | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/troubleshooting).

- Webhook misconfiguration: ensure the webhook URL is HTTPS, publicly reachable, configured on PhonePe merchant console, and set to accept POST JSON with Basic auth; always verify the Basic auth header on receipt [Webhook Handling | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/mobile-app-integration/standard-checkout-mobile/webhook-handling).

- Domain/referrer mismatch: production flows require whitelisted domains and proper redirectUrl/callbackUrl values; do not use localhost in production and ensure redirect/callback domains match merchant configuration [Troubleshooting | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/troubleshooting).

- Token expiration handling: cache OAuth tokens until expiry and refresh proactively to avoid 401 Unauthorized errors during peak flows [PhonePe Auth docs](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-integration-website).

Operational checklist before going live

- Confirm merchant KYC and production credentials from PhonePe merchant portal [PhonePe Payment Gateway API Documentation](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/website-integration/standard-checkout/api-integration/api-integration-website).
- Replace sandbox endpoints with production endpoints and update all credentials accordingly [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).
- Ensure X-VERIFY logic uses production salt key and salt index precisely [Calculating X-VERIFY](https://developer.phonepe.com/switch/documentation/calculating-x-verify).
- Configure and verify webhook endpoint with Basic auth credentials in PhonePe dashboard and test webhook deliveries in sandbox first [Webhook Handling | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/mobile-app-integration/standard-checkout-mobile/webhook-handling).
- Run end-to-end sandbox test cases (success, failure, pending) using PhonePe Test App and test cards [UAT Sandbox | PhonePe](https://developer.phonepe.com/payment-gateway/uat-testing-go-live/uat-sandbox).

